    ,('Knight Foundation','North Tryon Vision and Master Planning Process',75000.0,NULL,NULL,'donation log','Communities','https://knightfoundation.org/grants/6262',NULL,'Grant period: 02/01/2014 - 12/31/2014; project team: Foundation for the Carolinas; goal: For a master planning process to re-imagine the north end of uptown Charlotte with its civic/cultural amenities as the city''s living room where residents and guests alike want to visit, engage and linger. The northeast section of downtown Charlotte is under-developed, yet includes some of the city''s important civic and cultural institutions. The area includes the community foundation''s headquarters, museums and the main branch of the public library.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL)
