    ,('Knight Foundation','Chattanooga Open Government Collaborative',50000.0,NULL,NULL,'donation log','Communities','https://knightfoundation.org/grants/6023',NULL,'Grant period: 09/01/2013 - 09/01/2014; part of the challenge: Knight Community Information Challenge; project team: Benwood Foundation; goal: Building on successful efforts to make city data more accessible, the Chattanooga Open Government Collaborative will use challenge funding to train key groups in using the available information. Building on successful efforts to make city data more accessible, the Chattanooga Open Government Collaborative will use challenge funding to train key groups, including journalists and city employees, in using the available information. The Chattanooga Public Library will create an online portal housing community data, and provide workshops and training on how best to use it to better the community. To start, the collaborative will focus on six community groups interested in a specific issue like public safety. At the end of one year, the collaborative hopes to have an engaged community of data consumers helping to identify needs and assist in designing and utilizing open data tools.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL)
