    ,('Knight Foundation','Detroit Soup',80000.0,NULL,NULL,'donation log','Arts','https://knightfoundation.org/grants/5313',NULL,'Grant period: 08/01/2012 - 07/31/2013; project team: Cityscape Detroit; goal: To support Detroit Soup''s expansion so that more young social entrepreneurs can engage, partner, and succeed with the broader community The Detroit SOUP project has steadily been helping great ideas in and for the city find a footing -- and funding. It''s grown over the years, but the idea remains simple: people gather once a month, and for $5, receive a meal and a chance to vote on which pitched idea should receive the funding collected from the entrance fee. It''s a simple idea, but a great one, and NBC Nightly News took notice, airing a Making a Difference segment about Detroit SOUP and facilitator Amy Kaherl on Wednesday night.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL)
