    ,('Knight Foundation','Poderopedia',200000.0,NULL,NULL,'donation log','Technology','https://knightfoundation.org/grants/5167',NULL,'Grant period: 09/01/2011 - 11/30/2013; part of the challenge: Knight News Challenge; project team: Tides Center; goal: To create an editorial and crowd-sourced database that allows visualizing the relationships among political, civic and business leaders To promote greater transparency in Chile, Poderopedia (Powerpedia) will be an editorial and crowdsourced database that highlights the links among the country’s elite. Using data visualization, the site will investigate and illustrate the connections among people, companies and institutions, shedding light on any conflicts of interests. Crowdsourced information will be vetted by professional journalists before it is posted. Entries will include an editorial overview, a relationship map and links to the sources of information.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL)
