    ,('Knight Foundation','Knight Theater: Arts and Science Council',5000000.0,NULL,NULL,'donation log','Arts','https://knightfoundation.org/grants/4033',NULL,'Grant period: 09/01/2006 - 09/01/2011; project team: Arts and Science Council-Charlotte/Mecklenburg Inc.; goal: For an operating endowment to support extensive new cultural facilities in downtown Charlotte, including a 1,200-seat theater to be named for John S. and James L. Knight The project includes a new Afro-American Cultural Center, a new uptown Mint Museum, the Bechtler Museum and the new Knight Theater as part of the Wachovia First Street Cultural Campus — a mixed-use development scheduled to open in late 2008. The arts facilities will reside at the heart of a major office/residential complex. The 1,200-seat Knight Theater fills a needed gap in performance hall space, providing a home for N.C. Dance Theater and freeing up performance time in the larger Performing Arts Center for the symphony and opera, allowing all to grow artistically and financially.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL)
